384
00:19:24,550 --> 00:19:25,717
Yeah. We'll, that can't
be a coincidence.

385
00:19:25,785 --> 00:19:27,025
Our fake dad from the wedding's

386
00:19:27,086 --> 00:19:28,553
got to be tied to us somehow.

387
00:19:28,621 --> 00:19:29,955
Wedding photographer's
already pulling photographs.

388
00:19:30,022 --> 00:19:31,662
Hopefully we'll get
a match in the system.

389
00:19:31,724 --> 00:19:33,959
Hotel has the room listed
as empty,

390
00:19:34,026 --> 00:19:35,727
so we think that our hooker used

391
00:19:35,795 --> 00:19:37,562
a maid's card key to get in.

392
00:19:37,630 --> 00:19:39,331
Oh. The maid's body
is in the closet.

393
00:19:39,398 --> 00:19:40,932
Hotel security video?

394
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,434
Disabled during the attack.

395
00:19:42,502 --> 00:19:44,603
Our girl knew what
she was doing.

396
00:19:44,670 --> 00:19:46,371
She wasn't alone.

397
00:19:46,439 --> 00:19:48,373
Definitely more than
one attacker.

398
00:19:48,441 --> 00:19:50,108
Most likely a male
based on the strength

399
00:19:50,176 --> 00:19:52,744
required to stage this,

400
00:19:52,812 --> 00:19:55,447
and they're not done.

401
00:19:55,515 --> 00:19:56,848
How do you know?

402
00:19:56,916 --> 00:20:00,552
They got some kind
of an agenda or message,

403
00:20:00,620 --> 00:20:02,454
and they know that they
haven't given us enough yet

404
00:20:02,522 --> 00:20:03,922
to figure it out.

405
00:20:06,592 --> 00:20:09,261
Which means the killing
is only beginning.

406
00:20:19,939 --> 00:20:23,508
You two have a room, you know?

407
00:20:23,576 --> 00:20:27,512
Our love cannot be
contained in a room.

408
00:20:27,580 --> 00:20:28,713
Hey. Andrew,
sweetie,

409
00:20:28,781 --> 00:20:30,649
do you have any more
of those yogurts?

410
00:20:30,716 --> 00:20:32,184
You mean my yogurts.

411
00:20:32,251 --> 00:20:34,386
Listen. I've clearly marked
my food in the fridge,

412
00:20:34,453 --> 00:20:36,021
so if you two could
just respect the labels.

413
00:20:36,088 --> 00:20:37,255
Heh heh.
Are you kidding?

414
00:20:37,323 --> 00:20:38,523
Not even a little bit.

415
00:20:38,591 --> 00:20:40,258
This little forced marriage
between us

416
00:20:40,326 --> 00:20:42,761
is going to work much better
if we have boundaries.

417
00:20:42,829 --> 00:20:46,097
Whatever, bro.

418
00:20:46,165 --> 00:20:47,566
Has he even come downstairs?

419
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:49,000
Did he ask how it went?

420
00:20:49,068 --> 00:20:50,702
No. He's in one
of his moods.

421
00:20:50,770 --> 00:20:53,972
Well, we have a job
to do, all right?

422
00:20:54,006 --> 00:20:55,774
Let's just get it done,

423
00:20:55,842 --> 00:20:57,943
and we can get our lives back.

424
00:20:59,779 --> 00:21:01,112
Ok.

425
00:21:04,584 --> 00:21:06,918
We're still adjusting
to the time difference.

426
00:21:06,986 --> 00:21:09,054
There is no time difference
between here and Ohio.

427
00:21:09,121 --> 00:21:11,223
Just give me a minute.
I'll rally.

428
00:21:11,290 --> 00:21:13,959
You know what?
Forget it.

429
00:21:14,026 --> 00:21:16,461
I'll do this one myself.

430
00:21:18,064 --> 00:21:19,798
We'll meet you later.

431
00:21:19,866 --> 00:21:20,947
Maybe I should go with him?

432
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,801
He's fine.

433
00:21:22,869 --> 00:21:25,737
That guy is one seriously
twisted individual.

434
00:21:32,145 --> 00:21:33,645
She was, uh...

435
00:21:33,713 --> 00:21:36,815
she was so beautiful.

436
00:21:36,883 --> 00:21:39,651
I can't believe that
she's really gone.

437
00:21:41,888 --> 00:21:44,055
I can't believe I'll
never get to hold her again

438
00:21:44,123 --> 00:21:45,624
or...

439
00:21:50,696 --> 00:21:53,565
I miss my little girl so much.

440
00:21:59,739 --> 00:22:03,775
Your daughter sounds like
she was really special.

441
00:22:03,843 --> 00:22:05,911
I lost my sister
a few weeks ago.

442
00:22:05,978 --> 00:22:09,014
Oh. I'm so sorry.

443
00:22:09,081 --> 00:22:11,450
Look. Uh, how about
I buy you a cup of coffee

444
00:22:11,517 --> 00:22:13,952
and we can talk about it?

445
00:22:14,020 --> 00:22:15,887
I got to say this guy's
pain felt so real.

446
00:22:15,955 --> 00:22:18,256
It's hard to believe
he was faking it.

447
00:22:18,324 --> 00:22:19,658
My guess is he
probably gets some kind

448
00:22:19,725 --> 00:22:21,193
of perverse pleasure from it,

449
00:22:21,260 --> 00:22:23,795
grew up unable to access
any kind of real emotion,

450
00:22:23,863 --> 00:22:24,963
so he started mimicking it,

451
00:22:25,031 --> 00:22:26,231
found out he had a true talent.

452
00:22:26,232 --> 00:22:27,666
Now he's Laurence Olivier.

453
00:22:27,733 --> 00:22:29,334
Ryan, security called.

454
00:22:29,402 --> 00:22:31,103
Gwen's downstairs.

455
00:22:31,170 --> 00:22:32,871
Ok. Be right back.

456
00:22:32,939 --> 00:22:34,439
Yeah.

457
00:22:37,910 --> 00:22:39,211
Hey.

458
00:22:39,278 --> 00:22:41,179
