542
00:28:44,442 --> 00:28:46,910
Agent Weston on his knees,

543
00:28:46,978 --> 00:28:48,345
and that's me

544
00:28:48,413 --> 00:28:50,047
right after I killed Giselle,

545
00:28:50,115 --> 00:28:52,015
Mark's adopted sister.

546
00:28:52,083 --> 00:28:53,550
The scenes that Luke
and Mark staged last year

547
00:28:53,618 --> 00:28:55,119
were more rudimentary.

548
00:28:55,186 --> 00:28:56,820
They used whatever was at
hand to pose the bodies.

549
00:28:56,888 --> 00:28:58,489
This is much more sophisticated.

550
00:28:58,556 --> 00:29:01,558
Which means that Mark
has his own followers now.

551
00:29:07,031 --> 00:29:08,298
Mark.

552
00:29:11,403 --> 00:29:13,670
We're getting ready
to go do the next one.

553
00:29:13,738 --> 00:29:15,239
You said you wanted to come.

554
00:29:18,410 --> 00:29:20,310
I can't.

555
00:29:20,378 --> 00:29:21,412
You sure?

556
00:29:21,479 --> 00:29:22,513
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

557
00:29:22,580 --> 00:29:23,514
Go ahead without me.

558
00:29:23,581 --> 00:29:24,681
Ok.

559
00:29:24,749 --> 00:29:26,417
No problem.

560
00:29:41,332 --> 00:29:43,267
What do you mean can't?

561
00:29:43,334 --> 00:29:45,002
Hey. This is
our revenge!

562
00:29:45,070 --> 00:29:47,204
You have to go!

563
00:29:47,272 --> 00:29:48,939
You don't understand.

564
00:29:49,007 --> 00:29:50,507
It's too painful.

565
00:29:50,575 --> 00:29:51,496
Painful? Try being shot

566
00:29:51,543 --> 00:29:53,944
in the friggin' head!

567
00:29:54,012 --> 00:29:55,979
I know. You're right. I'm sorry.

568
00:29:56,047 --> 00:29:57,727
Well, don't
be sorry, little bro.

569
00:29:57,782 --> 00:30:00,784
Be angry.

570
00:30:00,852 --> 00:30:02,352
Yeah.

571
00:30:02,420 --> 00:30:03,921
They killed us,

572
00:30:03,988 --> 00:30:05,122
and they covered it up.

573
00:30:05,190 --> 00:30:07,091
We've got to make them pay.

574
00:30:08,927 --> 00:30:10,994
We have alerts out on
Mark across the city.

575
00:30:11,062 --> 00:30:13,864
Why is he writing you've
lied at every scene?

576
00:30:13,932 --> 00:30:14,898
- Lied about what?
- I don't know.

577
00:30:14,966 --> 00:30:17,034
Ryan, I'm not buying--

578
00:30:17,102 --> 00:30:18,569
He's delusional, Gina.

579
00:30:18,636 --> 00:30:20,237
Him and his brother
were psychotically close.

580
00:30:20,305 --> 00:30:21,939
I can't imagine what
losing Luke has done

581
00:30:22,006 --> 00:30:24,875
to his fractured mind.

582
00:30:24,943 --> 00:30:28,245
But I do know who his next
target's gonna look like--

583
00:30:28,313 --> 00:30:29,880
Lily Gray.

584
00:30:32,751 --> 00:30:35,719
I don't get it. Why
would he sit this one out?

585
00:30:35,787 --> 00:30:38,355
I'd unleash hell
on earth if you got killed.

586
00:30:38,423 --> 00:30:41,158
I guess Mark's just a little
more sensitive than you.

587
00:30:43,361 --> 00:30:45,963
Why am I letting
you guys have all the fun?

588
00:30:47,999 --> 00:30:50,234
Come on. Let's go
kill some people.

589
00:31:07,260 --> 00:31:08,543
Max, got anything?

590
00:31:08,663 --> 00:31:10,729
Pull it up.
CCTV camera

591
00:31:10,797 --> 00:31:11,730
at the Lincoln
Center subway stop

592
00:31:11,798 --> 00:31:13,039
took this 20 minutes ago.

593
00:31:13,159 --> 00:31:14,459
Ok. He's not dressed
like that for fun.

594
00:31:14,527 --> 00:31:15,861
Any catered events
in the neighborhood?

595
00:31:15,928 --> 00:31:18,030
I mean, it's New York.
There's probably 50.

596
00:31:18,097 --> 00:31:19,564
We got to think like Mark.

597
00:31:19,632 --> 00:31:21,566
He's looking for a
doppelganger for his mother.

598
00:31:21,634 --> 00:31:23,669
Where would he go to find her?

599
00:31:23,736 --> 00:31:25,304
Got it. Art fundraiser
5 blocks from there.

600
00:31:25,371 --> 00:31:27,506
That's it!
Have NYPD meet us there.

601
00:31:27,573 --> 00:31:30,042
Code two, urgent!

602
00:31:55,101 --> 00:31:58,203
Luke, what about her?

603
00:31:58,271 --> 00:32:02,174
Hmm. Mom was way prettier.

604
00:32:02,241 --> 00:32:03,976
Yeah. You're right.

605
00:32:08,081 --> 00:32:09,948
Hi!

606
00:32:10,016 --> 00:32:11,617
Oh, she's perfect.

607
00:32:18,691 --> 00:32:20,158
We're on.

608
00:32:31,871 --> 00:32:33,372
Excuse me.

609
00:32:33,439 --> 00:32:34,673
Oh! Oh!

610
00:32:34,741 --> 00:32:36,775
I'm so sorry.

611
00:32:36,843 --> 00:32:38,610
It's ok.

612
00:32:38,678 --> 00:32:40,812
Um, I-I just need
a bathroom.

613
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:42,247
There's a big line
for the one up here,

614
00:32:42,315 --> 00:32:44,082
but the one downstairs is empty.

615
00:32:44,150 --> 00:32:45,384
Here. Let me
show you.

616
00:33:25,792 --> 00:33:27,159
You think Mark's gonna be here?

617
00:33:27,227 --> 00:33:28,927
It's his mother.
He won't leave

618
00:33:28,995 --> 00:33:30,762
this tableau to his followers.

619
00:33:34,367 --> 00:33:35,834
Ok. Fan out.

620
00:33:47,380 --> 00:33:49,381
FBI! Don't panic!

621
00:33:49,449 --> 00:33:50,716
Aah!

622
00:34:27,587 --> 00:34:29,555
Ugh! Agh!

623
00:34:46,940 --> 00:34:47,940
You ok?

624
00:34:48,007 --> 00:34:49,708
I'm good.
Where's Mark?!

625
00:34:49,776 --> 00:34:52,344
Sorry. You're too late.

626
00:35:06,526 --> 00:35:09,862
Let me out!

627
00:35:09,929 --> 00:35:12,264
Let me out, let me out!

628
00:35:13,633 --> 00:35:16,235
Let me out of here!

629
00:35:16,302 --> 00:35:19,571
Why you just sitting there?

630
00:35:19,639 --> 00:35:21,440
Come on.
Get out of the car.

631
00:35:21,508 --> 00:35:25,010
Come on!
Let me out!

632
00:35:25,078 --> 00:35:27,279
I don't think
I can do this, Luke.

633
00:35:27,347 --> 00:35:28,714
Well, you have to.

634
00:35:28,782 --> 00:35:31,583
You have to kill her
and finish what we started.

635
00:35:31,651 --> 00:35:33,152
Hey. Will you shut up!

636
00:35:35,255 --> 00:35:37,156
Nobody's talking to you.

637
00:35:46,733 --> 00:35:51,603
Will you come with me?

638
00:35:51,671 --> 00:35:54,540
Of course.

639
00:35:54,607 --> 00:35:56,675
I'm always with you.

640
00:35:59,379 --> 00:36:02,648
Yeah.

641
00:36:02,715 --> 00:36:04,083
Yeah. I know.

642
00:36:04,150 --> 00:36:05,551
Please!

643
00:36:28,108 --> 00:36:29,908
Please!

644
00:36:29,976 --> 00:36:31,710
Don't do this.

645
00:36:34,414 --> 00:36:35,647
No!

646
00:36:35,715 --> 00:36:38,283
Mom! Mom, I'm sorry.

647
00:36:42,222 --> 00:36:44,156
No. Get up.

648
00:36:44,224 --> 00:36:45,924
No, no, no. No.

649
00:36:45,992 --> 00:36:48,894
Hey. Don't go.
Don't go. Don't go.

650
00:36:48,962 --> 00:36:51,296
Please don't go.
Don't leave me.

651
00:36:51,364 --> 00:36:55,000
Please don't leave me.
I've been so lonely without you.

652
00:36:55,068 --> 00:36:57,102
Mom, I'm sorry.

653
00:36:57,170 --> 00:36:59,821
Please don't leave me.
Come back.

654
00:37:13,556 --> 00:37:15,057
Knock it off.

655
00:37:16,993 --> 00:37:19,595
Eh, you're no fun.

656
00:37:19,662 --> 00:37:22,130
When's the last time
you had a good cry?

657
00:37:22,198 --> 00:37:23,438
It can be incredibly cathartic.

658
00:37:23,466 --> 00:37:25,167
Yeah, but it's gonna make you

659
00:37:25,235 --> 00:37:27,182
all the wrong kinds
of friends in prison.

660
00:37:29,390 --> 00:37:31,473
You know, you should
have seen your face

661
00:37:31,541 --> 00:37:33,575
when I called you a murderer.

662
00:37:33,643 --> 00:37:34,743
I mean, you were shocked,

663
00:37:34,811 --> 00:37:37,679
but there was a part of you

664
00:37:37,747 --> 00:37:40,115
that welcomed it

665
00:37:40,183 --> 00:37:41,350
because you know it's true.

666
00:37:41,417 --> 00:37:42,517
Where's Mark Gray?

667
00:37:42,585 --> 00:37:46,355
Oh. Such
a sad story.

668
00:37:46,422 --> 00:37:48,257
His whole family was killed
by you and your friends.

669
00:37:48,324 --> 00:37:51,126
Yeah. What do you
care, huh?

670
00:37:51,194 --> 00:37:52,828
What's Mark to you?

671
00:38:09,145 --> 00:38:10,846
Thank you for coming.

672
00:38:10,914 --> 00:38:12,614
I didn't know who else to call.

673
00:38:21,190 --> 00:38:23,792
I'm a sucker
for a good revenge tale,

674
00:38:23,860 --> 00:38:25,928
but this--
heh heh heh--

675
00:38:25,995 --> 00:38:29,097
this is gonna be so much more.

676
00:38:29,165 --> 00:38:31,600
You have no idea what's coming.

677
00:38:31,668 --> 00:38:35,170
Ok. So this moment
may be new to you,

678
00:38:35,238 --> 00:38:37,139
but I've sat in this chair,

679
00:38:37,206 --> 00:38:38,807
and I've had this
very conversation,

680
00:38:38,875 --> 00:38:41,043
and the guy I had it
with is on death row,

681
00:38:41,110 --> 00:38:43,712
and I'm still here.

682
00:38:43,780 --> 00:38:48,483
So you can spare me
the scary proclamations.

683
00:38:48,551 --> 00:38:50,752
Do you have the time?

684
00:38:50,820 --> 00:38:54,089
Got someplace you got to be?

685
00:38:54,157 --> 00:38:57,326
No, but...

686
00:38:57,393 --> 00:38:58,894
you do.

687
00:39:33,930 --> 00:39:40,903
♪ Go your way ♪

688
00:39:40,970 --> 00:39:44,506
♪ I'll take the long way round ♪

689
00:39:44,574 --> 00:39:48,310
♪ oh, I'll find
my own way down ♪

690
00:39:48,378 --> 00:39:51,914
♪ oh, as I should ♪

691
00:39:57,086 --> 00:40:03,825
♪ hold your gates ♪

692
00:40:03,893 --> 00:40:07,162
♪ as croak in the midas touch ♪

693
00:40:07,230 --> 00:40:09,331
♪ a joke in the way
that we rust... ♪

694
00:40:09,399 --> 00:40:11,366
Hey. Stop it.

695
00:40:11,434 --> 00:40:13,035
We have to go home, ok?

696
00:40:13,102 --> 00:40:14,703
The FBI got Andrew. How
long before they get us?

697
00:40:14,771 --> 00:40:16,505
Calm down, Daisy.

698
00:40:16,573 --> 00:40:17,906
If we leave here
before we finish,

699
00:40:17,974 --> 00:40:19,808
what do you think's
gonna happen?

700
00:40:19,876 --> 00:40:22,477
Everything we have will be gone.

701
00:40:22,545 --> 00:40:25,080
We'll spend the rest of our
short lives on the run.

702
00:40:25,148 --> 00:40:26,515
He'll make sure of it.

703
00:40:26,583 --> 00:40:29,685
Mark has no idea
what's really going on.

704
00:40:29,752 --> 00:40:31,587
And we need to make sure
it stays that way.

705
00:40:31,654 --> 00:40:34,489
♪ And you'll find loss ♪

706
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:37,593
♪ and you'll fear
what you found ♪

707
00:40:39,662 --> 00:40:44,433
♪ when weather comes,
tear him down ♪

708
00:40:46,769 --> 00:40:49,938
♪ there will be
oats in the water ♪

709
00:40:50,006 --> 00:40:53,742
♪ there will be birds
on the ground ♪

710
00:40:53,810 --> 00:40:58,080
♪ there will be things
you never asked her ♪

711
00:40:58,147 --> 00:41:01,316
♪ oh, they tear at you now ♪

712
00:41:22,171 --> 00:41:28,577
♪ and hold your gates ♪

713
00:41:28,645 --> 00:41:32,281
♪ as croak in the midas touch ♪

714
00:41:32,348 --> 00:41:36,151
♪ a joke in the way
that we rust ♪

715
00:41:36,219 --> 00:41:38,787
♪ and breathe again ♪

716
00:41:44,093 --> 00:41:46,962
♪ And you'll find loss ♪

717
00:41:47,030 --> 00:41:50,032
♪ and you'll fear
what you found ♪

718
00:41:52,135 --> 00:41:56,705
♪ when weather comes,
tear him down ♪

719
00:41:59,208 --> 00:42:01,343
♪ there will be
oats in the water ♪

720
00:42:01,411 --> 00:42:04,246
I'm so glad you called me.

721
00:42:04,314 --> 00:42:07,582
Me, too.

722
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:09,651
I'm sorry.

723
00:42:12,088 --> 00:42:13,922
I shouldn't have
pressured you earlier.

724
00:42:13,990 --> 00:42:16,325
No. You were right.

725
00:42:16,392 --> 00:42:18,226
I was pushing you away.

726
00:42:18,294 --> 00:42:20,295
It's my pattern,

727
00:42:20,363 --> 00:42:23,899
and, uh, I don't want
to do it anymore.

728
00:42:26,502 --> 00:42:28,170
I need you.

729
00:42:30,106 --> 00:42:31,540
I need you, too.

730
00:42:52,929 --> 00:42:56,198
Today was hard.

731
00:42:56,265 --> 00:43:00,068
You really helped me
get through it.

732
00:43:00,136 --> 00:43:03,138
You did great.

733
00:43:03,206 --> 00:43:04,873
I'm proud of you.

734
00:43:11,948 --> 00:43:14,716
Thanks.

735
00:43:14,784 --> 00:43:16,351
Tomorrow will be easier.

736
00:43:16,419 --> 00:43:17,919
Are you kidding me?

737
00:43:17,987 --> 00:43:19,654
Tomorrow will be awesome

738
00:43:19,722 --> 00:43:23,658
because tomorrow
one of them dies.

739
00:43:27,163 --> 00:43:28,363
Hmm.

740
00:43:28,431 --> 00:43:30,198
Heh.

